        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down, Beckenham, Kent.</placeName>
                    <date>May 13th.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Frank</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Will you try to persuade Mr. Bartlett to do me a great favour (and if he will, report the result to me)—viz. to show to the Porcupine a live snake, observe whether the sight of the snake will make it rattle the quills on the tail, as Mr. Bartlett showed me that the Porcupine does when angered.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>You can read this note to Mr. Bartlett.</p>
<p>Yours affectionately | C. Darwin.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8332.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from A. D. Bartlett, 16 May 1872</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_300.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Abraham Dee Bartlett</ref> was superintendent of the Zoological Gardens, Regent’s Park, London.</note>
